jslog="191767;track:click;fYPJpb:W1tudWxsLCIvdHB1LyJdXQ==;"><div class="cws-jump-section" data-cws-menu-text="Overview" id="features"><p class="W42XEf fjX8Pb DUs80c">Overview</p><div class="" jscontroller="qSEpXb" jsaction="rcuQ6b:npT2md"><div class="" jsname="pofbfd" ssk='1#0'><div class="qPg9F  kJ4Wvd "><div class="AZgcHf" id="whatisatensorprocessingunittpu"><h3 class="MyvX5d">What is a Tensor Processing Unit (TPU)?</h3></div><div class="AlLELb EAoy4b"><div jsaction="rcuQ6b:npT2md" jscontroller="M0Q3Qb" class=" "><p>Google Cloud TPUs are custom-designed AI accelerators, which are optimized for training and inference of large AI models. They are ideal for a variety of use cases, such as chatbots, code generation, media content generation, synthetic speech, vision services, recommendation engines, personalization models, among others. </p></div></div></div></div><div class="" jsname="pofbfd" ssk='1#1'><div class="qPg9F  q1Plf "><div class="AZgcHf" id="whataretheadvantagesofcloudtpus"><h3 class="MyvX5d">What are the advantages of Cloud TPUs?</h3></div><div class="AlLELb EAoy4b"><div jsaction="rcuQ6b:npT2md" jscontroller="M0Q3Qb" class=" "><p>Cloud TPUs are designed to scale cost-efficiently for a wide range of AI workloads, spanning training, fine-tuning, and inference. Cloud TPUs provide the versatility to accelerate workloads on leading AI frameworks, including <a href="https://cloud.google.com/tpu/docs/run-calculation-pytorch" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">PyTorch</a>,<a href="https://cloud.google.com/tpu/docs/run-calculation-jax" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"> JAX</a>, and <a href="https://cloud.google.com/tpu/docs/run-calculation-tensorflow" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">TensorFlow</a>. Seamlessly orchestrate large-scale AI workloads through Cloud TPU integration in <a href="/kubernetes-engine" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Kubernetes Engine</a> (GKE). Customers looking for the simplest way to develop AI models can also leverage Cloud TPUs in <a href="/vertex-ai" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Vertex AI</a>, a fully-managed AI platform.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="" jsname="pofbfd" ssk='1#2'><div class="qPg9F  q1Plf "><div class="AZgcHf" id="whentousecloudtpus"><h3 class="MyvX5d">When to use Cloud TPUs?</h3></div><div class="AlLELb EAoy4b"><div jsaction="rcuQ6b:npT2md" jscontroller="M0Q3Qb" class=" "><p>Cloud TPUs are optimized for training large and complex deep learning models that feature many matrix calculations, for instance building large language models (LLMs). Cloud TPUs also have SparseCores, which are dataflow processors that accelerate models relying on embeddings found in recommendation models. Other use cases include healthcare, like protein folding modeling and drug discovery.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="" jsname="pofbfd" ssk='1#3'><div class="qPg9F  q1Plf "><div class="AZgcHf" id="howarecloudtpusdifferentfromgpus"><h3 class="MyvX5d">How are Cloud TPUs different from GPUs?</h3></div><div class="AlLELb EAoy4b"><div jsaction="rcuQ6b:npT2md" jscontroller="M0Q3Qb" class=" "><p>A GPU is a specialized processor originally designed for manipulating computer graphics. Their parallel structure makes them ideal for algorithms that process large blocks of data commonly found in AI workloads. <a href="https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/ai-machine-learning/what-makes-tpus-fine-tuned-for-deep-learning" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Learn more</a>.</p><p>A TPU is an application-specific integrated circuit (ASIC) designed by Google for neural networks. TPUs possess specialized features, such as the matrix multiply unit (MXU) and proprietary interconnect topology that make them ideal for accelerating AI training and inference.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="AXPOpb  znIWoc"><button type="button" class="tltOzc MExMre HceCQd qUoClb" track-name="view more" track-type="button" track-metadata-modifier="support"
